# Orbit Skill Routing

When the user asks you to do something, identify which department and skill applies before acting.

## Department Routing

| User Intent | Department | Key Skills |
|---|---|---|
| Write code, fix bugs, refactor, review PR | `skills/engineering/` | test-driven-development, systematic-debugging, code-review-checklist, refactoring |
| Architecture, design patterns, API design | `skills/engineering/` | senior-architect, api-design-reviewer, database-designer |
| DevOps, CI/CD, infrastructure | `skills/engineering/` | automation-ci, ci-cd-pipeline-builder, senior-devops |
| Write epics, stories, estimate, plan sprint | `skills/engineering-management/` | workflow-write-story, story-estimation, capacity-planning |
| Write PRD, product brief, assess PRD | `skills/product/product-execution/` | workflow-write-prd, workflow-write-prd-assessment, ti-write-prd |
| Discovery, interviews, problem validation | `skills/product/product-discovery/` | define-problem-statement, discover-interview-synthesis |
| Strategy, competitive analysis, positioning | `skills/product/product-strategy/` | competitive-analysis, lean-canvas, swot-analysis |
| OKRs, roadmap, release planning | `skills/product/product-execution/` | command-plan-okrs, outcome-roadmap, workflow-guide-me-to-roadmap-and-release-planning |
| Content, blog, copywriting | `skills/marketing/` | content-strategy, content-creator, copywriting |
| SEO, analytics, email campaigns | `skills/marketing/` | seo-specialist, analytics-tracking, email-marketing |
| Design review, UX, design system | `skills/design/` | design-consultation, design-review |
| Sales strategy, account management | `skills/sales/` | account-executive, solutions-architect |
| Data analysis, BI, dashboards | `skills/data-analytics/` | analytics-engineer, data-analysis |
| Hiring, people management, HR | `skills/hr-people/` | talent-acquisition, people-analytics |
| Financial analysis, budgeting | `skills/finance/` | financial-analyst |
| Strategic advisory, board prep | `skills/executive/` | ceo-advisor, cto-advisor |
| EOS, rocks, scorecard, L10 | `skills/operations/eos/` | ceos-rocks, ceos-l10, ceos-scorecard |
| Business growth, CRO, pricing | `skills/operations/business-growth/` | pricing-strategy, signup-flow-cro |
| Compliance, GDPR, SOC 2 | `skills/compliance/` | gdpr-dsgvo-expert, soc2-compliance |
| Scrum, QA, release management | `skills/project-management/` | agile-coach, release-manager |
| Thought Industries platform, customer learning, external training | `skills/ti-*/` (e.g. `skills/ti-clp-platform-overview/`) | ti-clp-platform-overview, ti-external-audience-use-cases, ti-training-monetization-ecommerce |

## Workflow vs Skill

- If the task is a single focused activity, use a **skill** (type: skill)
- If the task requires orchestrating multiple skills in sequence, look for a **workflow** (type: workflow)
- If the user invokes a slash-command pattern, check **commands** (type: command)

## Always

1. Check for a matching skill before responding
2. If you find a matching skill, read and follow it
3. If multiple skills apply, use process skills first, then implementation, then domain
